cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use BehR-WM in academic work, please cite the accompanying paper."
title: "BehR-WM: Behavior Consistency Reward for Text-Based World Models"
abstract: >-
  BehR-WM reframes world-model training for text-based interactive
  environments around functional equivalence with the real environment. Instead
  of maximizing Exact Match between predicted and real states, we optimize a
  tractable step-level proxy — the Behavior Consistency Reward (BehR) — which
  measures how much a frozen Reference Agent's likelihood of the logged next
  action shifts between the real state and the world-model-predicted state.
  Training with BehR improves task-level Consistency Ratio (CR) on WebShop and
  TextWorld while preserving or improving single-step prediction quality, and
  reduces false positives in offline surrogate evaluation.
authors:
